==English==

===Etymology===
Classical Latin, from Greek [[ορεξις]] ‘desire, appetite’, from [[ὀρἐγειν]] ‘stretch out, reach for, desire’.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ə'ɹɛksɪs/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|orex|es}}

# {{psychology}} the affective and conative character of mental activity as contrasted with its cognitive aspect; the appetitive aspect of an act.

